pol:EU_32018R1999_Title_0_Chapter_5_Section_3_Article_35 a pol:PolicyArticle ;
    rdfs:label "state of the energy union report" ;
    rdfs:comment "Article 35: state of the energy union report. (1) By 31 october of every year, the commission shall submit a state of the energy union report to the European Parliament and the Council. (2) The report includes the following elements: (a) assessment pursuant to article 29; (b) recommendations pursuant to article 34; (c) report on the functioning of the carbon market as per directive 2003/87/ec and article 21(2) thereof; (d) biennial report on union bioenergy sustainability from 2023; (e) biennial report on voluntary schemes under directive (eu) 2018/2001; (f) overall progress report on directive 2009/72/ec; (g) overall progress report on directive 2009/73/ec pursuant to article 52; (h) overall progress report on energy efficiency obligation schemes and alternative measures as per articles 7a and 7b of directive 2012/27/eu; (i) biennial overall progress report on the renovation of the national stock of buildings as per article 2a of directive 2010/31/eu; (j) every four years, an overall progress report on nearly zero-energy buildings in accordance with article 9(5) of directive 2010/31/eu; (k) overall progress report on the creation of a complete and operational energy market; (l) report on actual fuel quality and geographical coverage of fuels with maximum sulphur content of 10 mg/kg as per directive 98/70/ec; (m) progress report on competitiveness; (n) report on member states' progress towards phasing out energy subsidies, particularly for fossil fuels; (o) report on other issues relevant to the implementation of the energy union; (p) by 31 october 2019 and every four years thereafter, an assessment of the implementation of directive 2009/31/ec." ;
